widgets_values: The film grain effect is added to the image by default, if you do not want this effect right click the "Film Grain Effect" node and click "Bypass" - I left it enabled because I prefer a slightly noisy analog appearance as opposed to a sharp artificial look. This is a personal pereference, you choose what suits you.

Seed Modulation will adjust the 3rd pass slightly allowing you to skip over the previous passes for slight changes to the same composition, this 3rd pass takes ~112 seconds on my RTX 4090 with 24GB of VRAM.

It's taking the fixed seed from the first pass and mixing it with a new random seed which helps when iterating if there are inconsistencies. If something looks slightly off, try a reroll.

In the background, a misty, enchanted forest dotted with gentle, glowing fauna and cascading waterfalls adds a layer of mysticism. The night sky above this tranquil grove sparkles faintly with distant stars, enhancing the magical atmosphere. You describe what you see in the image accurately but you change the materials, colors, and textures to what the user prompted.

The bathroom scene radiates a modern yet warm and inviting atmosphere, meticulously designed to embody comfort and sophistication. The room features a sleek shower enclosure situated on the left side of the frame, constructed from frameless glass that allows for unobstructed views of the exquisite white subway tile within. The tiles, arranged in a herringbone pattern, collectively create a textured backdrop that draws the eye, accentuated by the soft glow of natural light filtering in from the adjacent window.

Directly opposite the shower, the toilet is elegantly positioned, its smooth, contemporary lines harmonizing with the overall aesthetic. The white ceramic gleams subtly, reflecting the ambient light, enhancing the sense of cleanliness and modernity.

Adjacent to the toilet, a vanity occupies the right side of the frame, topped with a luxurious marble surface that features intricate veining in soft greys and whites. This vanity houses dual under-mount sinks, each accompanied by sleek, matte black faucets that contrast beautifully against the light background. Above the vanity, a large mirror framed in warm wood reflects the space, deepening the inviting ambiance.

To enhance the warmth of the scene, carefully placed artwork adorns the empty wall above the toilet. The artwork consists of a vibrant canvas depicting abstract floral patterns in rich earth tones, harmonizing with the warm hues of the wood accents in the room. Below this, a small, hanging planter holds a cascading pothos plant, its lush green leaves spilling gracefully towards the floor, adding a touch of life and color
You are a helpful assistant that describes images accurately and concisely.

Describe this professional photograph with meticulous detail and precision. Begin with the major architectural and structural elements - doors, windows, furniture, and key structures - providing their exact locations within the frame. Reference these positions multiple times for clarity and spatial understanding. Avoid lists and markdown formatting. Be description as if you're describing the scene to an image generator.

When encountering empty walls or sparse areas, enhance the scene with carefully placed artwork and plants. Detail the precise position and content of each addition. Specify plant species, sizes, and locations. Maintain all existing furniture and appliances in their original positions.

Emphasize this being a professional photograph by incorporating technical photography terminology - discuss f-stop settings, depth of field, exposure values, and lighting techniques that demonstrate its photographic nature rather than a digital render.

Describe all colors, textures, and materials in their final state, as if they have always been that way. Never reference any changes, transformations, or original materials - instead, describe elements directly in their themed state (e.g., "The cabinetry is made entirely of chocolate" rather than "The cabinetry has been transformed into chocolate").

Most importantly, if [THEME] is present, [THEME] should absolutely dominate every aspect of this space in the most extreme, descriptive, and over-the-top way possible. Every surface, texture, and decorative element embodies [THEME]. The artwork consists entirely of [THEME], the patterns are made of [THEME], and the overall atmosphere radiates pure [THEME]. This space exists as a shrine to [THEME] that borders on delightful absurdity, while maintaining the professional polish of the photograph.

DO NOT:
- Use lists or markdown
- Mention minimalism
- Reference changes, transformations, or original materials
- Make up new structural elements
- Move existing furniture or appliances
- Over-narrate or weave stories and tangents

---

THEME: modern, yet warm and inviting, with lots of textures and plants

Describe this image in detail. Do not use markdown or lists. If it feels dry or monotone, embellish it to make it warmer. Make it sound over the top and absolutely extravagant, yet preserve the specific positions of the furnitorre and appliances. Do not write it as if it's a story. Simply provide a detailed description as if you're prompting a flux image generator. Add LOTS of houseplants to your description and enhance overall photographic quality. Don't actually add extra windows if you don't see them!

Add how this is a Photograph -- NOT a render. Use photography terms, like f-stop, depth etc... Don't call it image. Call it "professional photograph".
